HEADWORD: Phenylamine
<hw>Phe`nyl*am"ine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Phenyl</ets> + <ets>amine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Any one of certain class of organic bases regarded as formed from
ammonia by the substitution of phenyl for hydrogen.</def>⟦br⟧
